history.content: I do not believe there is any plan to webcast any summer session courses.  Due to that and the speed of content dissemination, I have not heard of any plan for the department to override summer course conflicts. You'll need to be able to attend the class.

children.subject:
That's up to the instructor.

This is usually the case and seems probable for CS61C/CS70, but they're under no obligation to maintain this.

OP here,

Well, that makes things really difficult to find two classes that don't override. I will have to take CS 61C instead and sadly its quite full right now.

I was also wondering if we are able to sign up for a conflicted discussion time but attend another. In the end I feel that there will be rooms in other discussion however just a lot of time conflicts.

history.content:
I'm trying to take CS 70 (session C) and ESPM 50AC (session A) which session A and C overlaps for two weeks.

CS 70 and ESPM 50AC has overlapping lecture times. Being a lower div CS course I assume it is webcasted. I have tried contacting CalCentral and we all know their famous response time.

Of course, I have went to the enrollment and tried adding the time conflict which would notify the system to send me a time-conflict request form. I contacted CalCentral why I haven't received it yet (its been over a month). 

For CS 61B I was able to resolve my conflict through EECS (this piazza page actually). I was wondering if I am able to resolve this conflict here as well.
